    "body": "> @orenyodfat I was about to implement this issue and realized that the internal function is not necessary if the use case is to run it in the constructor (or in an initializer function ran in the context of a constructor): the existing `transferOwnership` can already be used in this situation. I looked at your link and this is exactly what you're doing. So I'm a bit lost now: what is your issue exactly? Does the contract that you just shared not work?\r\n> \r\n> I'm sorry I didn't mention this earlier. I was sure I had considered it and that it didn't work for some reasson.\r\n\r\nit now works. (I did not noticed that that the transferOwnership use msgSender()) .. .\r\nthough still I think there is a room  for optimisation , as with the \"workaround\" there are 2 storage writes. (for the _owner).",
